Exits.

Use exits when you want to know where you can move from the current room.

Common forms:

exits
  List visible exits from your current room.

look
  With screenreader support on, look also includes the visible exits in the room
  summary.

Movement commands are usually directions, such as north, south, east, west, up,
down, enter, exit, northeast, northwest, southeast, and southwest.

Some rooms hide exits until you examine the room or an object in the room. If
you feel stuck, try look, then look at anything interesting mentioned by the
room.
